"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.4.10\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.4.10</span> 标题：浇酒祭的壶（jar for the wine offering, libation vessel）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：מְנַקִּית</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：mnaqith)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:29\">EXO 25:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:16\">EXO 37:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:7\">NUM 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:19\">JER 52:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：קַשְׂוָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：qaswah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:29\">EXO 25:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:16\">EXO 37:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:7\">NUM 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:17\">1CH 28:17</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0457_libation.jpg\" alt=\"捧着奠酒瓶的陶瓷像\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">捧着奠酒瓶的陶瓷像 (© Mary Harrsch from Springfield, Oregon, USA, CC BY 2.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>在帐幕和圣殿里献上的浇酒祭，是把酒倒出来作为供物献给上帝。浇酒祭要用到两个容器，酒从一个容器倒进另一个容器。两个容器都放在摆设供饼的桌子上（参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.3.5 摆放供饼的桌子 (table for consecrated bread)&lt;REALIA:4.3.5&gt;</a> ），而且总是与这张桌子一同提到。第一个容器是一种壶或罐子（希伯来文<em>qaswah</em> ），第二个容器是一个小碗（希伯来文<em>mnaqith</em> ）。这两件器具都是金子做的。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:29\">EXO 25:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:16\">EXO 37:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:7\">NUM 4:7</a> ：在这些经文中，希伯来文<em>mnaqith</em> 和<em>qaswah</em> 与一个动词同时出现，这个动词通常是“倒出来作为浇酒祭”的意思。根据犹太人的传统，这个动词还有另一种意思；按照这种意思，<em>mnaqith</em> 和<em>qaswah</em> 被解释为遮盖和保护供饼所用框架的一部分。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:29\">EXO 25:29</a> b中，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 英文意为“用来浇酒的壶和碗”，然而按照上述第二种意思，这句话也可以译成“用来遮盖它们的杆和边框”；但是，我们查阅的所有译本（包括<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> ）都没有采纳这种译法。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
